---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { Icon } from 'astro-icon/components';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy - FastShip">
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-white">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="py-20 bg-gray-50">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
        <div class="text-center max-w-4xl mx-auto">
          <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold text-black mb-6">
            Privacy Policy
          </h1>
          <p class="text-xl text-black mb-8">
            Your privacy is important to us. Learn how we protect and handle your data.
          </p>
          <div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-4">
            <Icon class="w-8 h-8 text-black" name="bx:shield" />
            <Icon class="w-8 h-8 text-black" name="bx:lock" />
            <Icon class="w-8 h-8 text-black" name="bx:user-check" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Privacy Policy Content -->
    <section class="py-16 bg-white">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto prose prose-lg">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-8 mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-black mb-4">FastShip – Privacy Policy</h2>
          </div>

          <p class="text-black mb-8">
            FastShip values your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your data when you use our website and services. By using FastShip, you agree to the practices described in this policy.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-black mb-4">01 Information We Collect</h3>
          <p class="text-black mb-4">We may collect the following types of information:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-black mb-6">
            <li><strong>Personal Information:</strong> Name, email address, phone number, payment details, and other information you provide during registration or transactions.</li>
            <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Information about how you access and use FastShip, including IP address, browser type, device information, and activity logs.</li>
            <li><strong>Cookies & Tracking Data:</strong> To improve user experience, analyze trends, and personalize content.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-black mb-4">02 How We Use Your Information</h3>
          <p class="text-black mb-4">We use the information we collect for purposes such as:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-black mb-6">
            <li>Providing and maintaining FastShip services.</li>
            <li>Processing payments and managing subscriptions.</li>
            <li>Enhancing user experience and improving our platform.</li>
            <li>Communicating updates, offers, and support messages.</li>
            <li>Ensuring compliance with legal obligations and protecting against fraud.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-black mb-4">03 Sharing & Disclosure of Information</h3>
          <p class="text-black mb-4">We do not sell or rent your personal information. However, we may share your data in the following cases:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-black mb-6">
            <li><strong>With Service Providers:</strong> For payment processing, hosting, analytics, and customer support.</li>
            <li><strong>For Legal Reasons:</strong> When required by law, regulation, or government request.</li>
            <li><strong>Business Transfers:</strong> In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-black mb-4">04 Data Protection & Security</h3>
          <p class="text-black mb-6">
            We implement reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, loss, misuse, or disclosure. However, no method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-black mb-4">05 Cookies & Tracking Technologies</h3>
          <p class="text-black mb-4">FastShip uses cookies and similar technologies to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-black mb-4">
            <li>Remember user preferences.</li>
            <li>Improve performance and functionality.</li>
            <li>Analyze traffic and usage patterns.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-black mb-6">
            You can disable cookies through your browser settings, but some features of FastShip may not function properly.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-black mb-4">06 Your Rights</h3>
          <p class="text-black mb-4">Depending on your location, you may have rights under applicable data protection laws, such as:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-black mb-4">
            <li>Right to access and request a copy of your personal data.</li>
            <li>Right to correct inaccurate information.</li>
            <li>Right to request deletion of your data.</li>
            <li>Right to restrict or object to data processing.</li>
            <li>Right to withdraw consent (where applicable).</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-black mb-6">To exercise these rights, please contact us at contact@fastship.work.</p>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-black mb-4">07 International Data Transfers</h3>
          <p class="text-black mb-6">
            If you access FastShip from outside your home country, your data may be transferred and stored in countries with different data protection laws. We ensure that such transfers comply with applicable regulations.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-black mb-4">08 Retention of Data</h3>
          <p class="text-black mb-6">
            We retain your personal data only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this policy, unless a longer retention period is required by law.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-black mb-4">09 Third-Party Links</h3>
          <p class="text-black mb-6">
            FastShip may contain links to third-party websites. We are not responsible for the privacy practices or content of such sites.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-black mb-4">10 Changes to Privacy Policy</h3>
          <p class="text-black mb-6">
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on our website, and the updated policy will take effect upon posting.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-black mb-4">11 Contact Us</h3>
          <p class="text-black mb-4">If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us:</p>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6">
            <p class="text-black mb-2">📧 contact@fastship.work</p>
            <p class="text-black">📍 FastShip Services</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA Section -->
    <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 text-center">
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-black mb-6">
            Questions About Privacy?
          </h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-black mb-8">
            We're committed to transparency and protecting your data. Contact us if you have any questions.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
            <a href="mailto:contact@fastship.work" 
               class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-black text-white px-8 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-gray-800 transition-colors">
              <Icon class="w-5 h-5" name="bx:envelope" />
              Contact Us
            </a>
            <a href="/terms-of-service" 
               class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 border border-black text-black px-8 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-black hover:text-white transition-colors">
                             <Icon class="w-5 h-5" name="bx:file" />
              Terms of Service
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
